The paper deals with graph reconstruction using discrete Morse theory, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The reconstruction involves both topological and geometric aspects, which suggests categories such as computational geometry (cs.CG), graph theory (cs.GR), and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper proposes a new noise model for the density function, which could also fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
